methods.applicationDir:
The application directory. Application mode must be enabled.

:return: (java.nio.file.Path) the application dir
methods.find:
Parses the list of application configs found by searching the directory specified by the system property
 Application.dir. A path is considered an application file when the name ends in .app, the file is
 readable, and the file is regular
 and not a link. The resulting configs will be sorted lexicographically based on file name. Application mode must
 be enabled.

:return: (java.util.List<io.deephaven.appmode.ApplicationConfig>) the list of application configs
methods.isApplicationModeEnabled:
True if application mode is enabled; set system property ApplicationConfigImpl.APPLICATION_DIR_PROP to
 enable.

:return: (boolean) true if application mode is enabled
methods.isEnabled: :return: (boolean) whether this particular application is enabled
